node.text:
This week, instead of sipping, we’re snacking. Contributing editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker) is back in Riviera Nayarit, Mexico at One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) cooking with Executive Chef Olivier Deboise (@olideboise). Chef’s Fire-Roasted Gratinated Oysters are sure to be a hit at your next summer party.
.
Ingredients:
½ dozen oysters
1 ½ oz butter
1 ½ oz aged goat cheddar
½ tsp shallots, diced
½ tsp Serrano chili, chopped
½ tsp epazote, julienned
Zest of 1 lemon
Zest of 1 lime 
.
Top each oyster with ¼ oz of butter and divide the chopped ingredients, lemon zest, and lime zest among the oysters. Top with grated aged goat cheddar. Grill over a medium to low flame for three to four minutes and brûlée for one and a half minutes. Serve hot.

node.title: These Fire-Roasted Oysters Are the Perfect Summer Appetizer

node.text: Next up on Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) visits One&Only Mandarina (@oomandarina) in beautiful Riviera Nayarit, Mexico, where Mixologist Ivan Aguilar shows us how to make one of his favorite cocktails. Of course, no trip to Mexico is complete without tequila, so naturally, that’s our spirit of choice for this episode. In fact, Ivan shows us that tequila can be used to add a twist to cocktails that traditionally use other liquors. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Calling All Tequila Lovers, This Cocktail Could Become Your New Favorite

node.text: On the latest episode of Sipping With, Sean (@travelingnewyorker) heads to his hometown of Buffalo, New York to learn how to make three different summertime cocktails from head bartender at Lloyd Taco Factory (@lloydtacofactory), Jon Wheelock (@jwheels1). We won't give away what they're making, but we will say, if gin is your spirit of choice, you're in for a treat. We hope you’ll follow along and sip with us at home. Cheers!

node.title: Elevate Your Next Summer Get-together With These Cocktail Recipes

node.text: Introducing Sipping With, a new series hosted by Contributing Editor Sean Flynn (@travelingnewyorker), who’s taking us behind the bar at world-renowned restaurants, hotels, and resorts to see how the best in the business craft specialty cocktails. Cheers!

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: the island of Amorgos, Greece. The Greek Islands are on just about everyone's bucket list. But like many of the world’s most photogenic destinations, over-tourism has become a real issue. Luckily, there are more than 200 inhabited islands in Greece, meaning you can get all of the beauty and none the crowds on some of the lesser-known islands, like Amorgos. Come along! Tour by @_thebluewalk

node.title: This Greek Island Has All of the Beauty and None of the Crowds

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: Paris, France. A city that needs no introduction, Paris may as well be synonymous with food, culture, fashion, and architecture. Despite being a bucket-list destination for millions of people, the French capital still holds plenty of hidden secrets beyond the Eiffel Tower and world-class museums. Join us on this walking tour to see for yourself. Tour by @walkstours

node.title: Jet Off to Paris From the Comfort of Your Home on This Virtual Walking Tour

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: The Underground Railroad Tour of Alexandria, Virginia. We’ll hear stories as recorded by William Still, an abolitionist based in Philadelphia, where many enslaved people fled to from Alexandria. These stories will give insight into the historic work of the Underground Railroad and the experiences of the individuals who traveled it in hopes of escaping slavery. Come along. Tour by @manumissiontour

node.text: In this new video series, Walk With T+L, we'll be taking you on some of the best walking tours across the globe. On this episode: The Holiday Tour of New York City. In a normal year, millions of visitors would be traveling to the Big Apple to see it decked out for the holiday season. This year, however, most of those visitors will be staying home, which is why we decided to bring New York City’s holiday cheer to you. Join us as we visit the Rockefeller Christmas Tree, Radio City Music Hall, and more. Happy holidays! Tour by @topdogtoursnyc

node.title: Stuck at Home This Christmas? Join Us on the Holiday Tour of New York City

node.text: London has acquired an unfair reputation for bland food, when in fact, diversity and high quality local produce are boosting its ever-growing food scene. Even better, the city’s magical aesthetic often translates into restaurant decor that will renew your sense of wonder. node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Dry Tortugas National Park. May be an image of ocean and text that says 'Dry Tortugas National Park Is 99% Underwater and That's Exactly Why It's a Must-visit'.

node.text: Ever heard of a national park that’s 99% underwater, located 70 miles from civilization, and accessible only by seaplane or boat? Enter Dry Tortugas National Park, one of the most remote in the entire U.S. National Park System. Get our guide at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Big Sur, California with @emmett_sparling. May be an image of coast, nature and ocean.

node.text: When it comes to road trips, California is hard to top. The land of fair weather always seems to deliver that carefree, top-down experience. Get our list of road trips that will take you from Big Sur to the Sierras at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @emmett_sparling

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Rye, East Sussex with @fayazey. May be an image of the Cotswolds, tree, brick wall and outdoors.

node.text: England is divided into three sections, each with its own unique history, popular cities and fabulous nightlife. Planning a trip for when we can easily hop across the pond again? Get our England travel guide at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @fayazey

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in France. May be an image of ocean and text that says '7 Family Vacations That Everyone Should Do at Least Once'.

node.text: Planning a family vacation can be stressful. There's so much to consider, from finding family-friendly accommodations to choosing a destination with activities that your whole crew will enjoy. That's why we’ve rounded up a list of the best family vacations at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in La Marquise with @a_ontheroad. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: While people travel to Paris to see the Louvre, climb the Eiffel Tower, or see Notre-Dame, the real magic is found in the streets. Check out our newly updated Paris travel guide at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @a_ontheroad

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Sicily with @lumadeline. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: Sicily is finally being discovered for the magical destination that it is, and we think it's time you saw for yourself. Find out what there is to see and do while you're there at the link in bio. 🍝 #tlpicks courtesy of @lumadeline

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Alicante, Spain. May be an image of outdoors and text that says '9 of the Best Places to Retire in Europe'.

node.text: In recent years, more seniors have been considering retirement abroad, and quite a few have actually made the move. If you want to be one of them, check out our list of the best places to retire in Europe at the link in bio.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Travel + Leisure in Colorado with @lou_wanders. May be an image of tree and nature.

node.text: Looking to plan an end-of-summer adventure? Find a list of the best Colorado towns for a warm-weather vacation at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @lou_wanders

node.text: Bali is known as the island of the gods for a reason. Planning a trip? Get our travel guide at the link in bio. #tlpicks courtesy of @merrwatson
